-- Taiwan Stocks: Asia Cement, Gold Circuit Electronics, Pegatron
-- B y   W e i y i   L i m
-- 2012-04-16T01:48:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-16/taiwan-stocks-asia-cement-gold-circuit-electronics-pegatron.html
Shares of the following companies
had  unusual  moves in  Taiwan trading . Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 9:32 a.m. local time in Taipei.  The benchmark Taiex Index fell 0.6 percent to 7,744.50,
poised for the biggest decline since April 9.  Asia Cement Corp. (1102)  (1102 TT) lost 1.4 percent to NT$36.05,
headed for the biggest decline since April 5. Its Hong Kong-
listed unit, Asia Cement China Holdings Corp., said the group is
expected to record a “substantially” lower net profit in the
first quarter this year compared with the same period a year
earlier .  Gold Circuit Electronics Ltd. (2368)  (2368 TT) retreated 1.3
percent to NT$7.59. The company signed NT$2.2 billion ($74.5
million) of loans with a group of eight banks, according to data
compiled by Bloomberg.  Pegatron Corp. (4938)  (4938 TT) gained 1.1 percent to NT$44.95,
poised for the highest close since March 30. The electronics
maker had its share-price estimate increased 43 percent at
Citigroup Inc. on its earnings outlook. The brokerage kept its
buy rating on the stock.  To contact the reporter on this story:
